utschen Kommunismus und das deutsch-sowjetische Verhältnis systematisch und transnational zu beleuchten.  aThanks to the archival revolution, relations between the Comintern, the Soviet government and the KPD (German Communist Party) now appear in a new light. Careful analyses contextualize this history against the backdrop of the simultaneously published volume of sources. This project undertaken by the German-Russian Historical Commission contributes significantly to a transnational understanding of German communism and German-Soviet relations.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCommunismzGermanyxHistory. 0aCommunismzSoviet UnionxHistory. 4aArchivrevolution. 4aDeutschland. 4aKomintern. 4aKommunismus. 4aRussland. 4aSowjetunion. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh  aComintern.  aCommunism.  aGermany.  aRussia.  aSoviet Union.  aarchival revolution.1 aBayerlein, Bernhard H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBayerlein, Bernhard H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDrabkin, Jakov, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrabkin, Jakov, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGalkin, Aleksandr, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGalkin, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeber, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 